	   <form action=http://www1.allakhazam.com/perl/strategy/mrate.pl name=f104314302459246><tr><td id=headerrow><a id=sj href=item.html?item=5628&mid=104314302459246>RE: Reason for change</a> <a id=fs8 href=item.html?item=5628&mid=104314302459246#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=93804><span id=Scholar>ubvmadman, Eater of Souls</span></a>, <span id=Scholar>Scholar</span><br><span id=notbold>37 posts</td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Tue, Jan 21st 5:25 AM 2003</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Excellent<span id=notbold>[4.75]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>Too many were finding their way to lowly level 20s. Since no &quot;ubers&quot; or highbys would be caught dead with a non-magical weapon, the non-magic Reaver were gotten rid off at fire sale prices (2K to 5K) at the bazaar. Lowbys that bought it at such prices realised that 90% of the content out there DON'T REQUIRE MAGIC WEAPONS. Thus, what was a neat idea (conditional high end weapon that could only be used on non-magic mobs) became a potential game-breaking weapon if too many of them flowed downwards. A &quot;reverse nerf&quot; occured, the weapon became magical, demand for the weapon has risen amongst the high end crowd and the prices have risen accordingly to 10K+ plats out of the hands of lowly (but poor) players.<br><br>All is well in the game now....<br>&nbsp;<br></td></tr>
