	   <tr><td colspan=2>At the moment I am a 45 SK and I have been wielding my Reaver since the twenties (yes, there is a damage cap until you hit level 30 even, i hit max 87 at level 29 and easily into 120's at level 30).&nbsp;&nbsp;It may not be an 'all purpose' weapon, but in using it I have found that it is able to hit nearly every mob I have encountered, exceptions being some undead, a few luclin mobs, and most named.  This probably is not your weapon if you prefer spending your EQ time doing raids, being as that is when you will encounter a good many of the mobs that Reaver can not hit. However, if you like to xp, this wep will serve you well.<br>As an SK this weapon has made soloing extremely easy for me, most of the time i do not even need to fear kite, even at 45 ( i also wear a fungi which helps that ).  If you like grouping for exp i found mobs in lake of ill omen, FM, OT, DL, most KC and most VL to pose no immunity to the reaver, i have heard that the non named in ToV even can be hit with it.  The ratio as you can see is incredible at 40/40, the resists are good if your fighting casters, most of which i have found can still be hit by reaver.  If you are of level to take down the statue you should already have a decent weapon/set of weapons at your disposal, keep these to use as your backups should you stumble across one of the mobs that it can't hit.  If you are buying this weapon, spend an extra 1-2k on a velium weapon from DN to have a 30/40 in your bag.  All in all, Reaver may not be a weapon for everyone, but should you choose to buy and use one I highly doubt you will regret that choice.<br><br>oh, btw.... much fun in duels and PvP as well I would imagine!<br><br>Safe travels and fun keeling to ya<br><br>Weewo Wowwie<br>45 SK of the Nameless Server<br>Snogirl Iceblade<br>51 War of the Nameless<br>&nbsp;<br></td></tr>
